        },
        {
          "body": "Republic City",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "external": false,
            "href": "/wiki/Republic_City",
            "page": "Republic_City"
          }
        }
      ],
      "section": [
        "Poppy Beifong",
        "History",
        "Later life"
      ],
      "text": "In 141 AG, Poppy and Lao gave shelter to their granddaughter Suyin after she was sent away from Republic City by her mother to avoid having to go to jail for participating in a robbery."
    },
    {
      "body": "Poppy Beifong was a cheery and polite woman. Poppy cared deeply for her daughter and only wished for her safety, but she was very protective of her, even going as far as hiding her existence from the rest of the town, which she believed to be the only way to keep Toph safe. She also preferred to be submissively supportive of her husband's decisions regarding the care of their daughter, rather than making decisions herself.",
      "links": [],
      "section": [
